    {
      "id": "el_17",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 535,
      "y": 403,
      "width": 414,
      "height": 219,
      "text": "Period 4: 2(2,4,8,6) 3(3,9,7,1) 7(7,9,3,1) 8(8,4,2,6)\nPeriod 2: 4(4,6)  9(9,1)\nPeriod 1: 0,1,5,6 always same\n\nFind unit digit of a^n:\n  n mod period = r -> pick r-th in cycle\n  If r=0, use LAST value in cycle!\n\nWHY: Multiplying by same digit repeats unit digits\n  in a fixed cycle (mod 10 arithmetic)\n\nEx: 8^15 → period=4, 15 mod 4=3 → 3rd in (8,4,2,6) →\n2 ✓\n  Verify: 8^3=512, unit digit=2 ✓",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 1700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 17,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f4"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Period 4: 2(2,4,8,6) 3(3,9,7,1) 7(7,9,3,1) 8(8,4,2,6)\nPeriod 2: 4(4,6)  9(9,1)\nPeriod 1: 0,1,5,6 always same\n\nFind unit digit of a^n:\n  n mod period = r -> pick r-th in cycle\n  If r=0, use LAST value in cycle!\n\nWHY: Multiplying by same digit repeats unit digits\n  in a fixed cycle (mod 10 arithmetic)\n\nEx: 8^15 → period=4, 15 mod 4=3 → 3rd in (8,4,2,6) →\n2 ✓\n  Verify: 8^3=512, unit digit=2 ✓",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
