      "width": 398,
      "height": 234,
      "text": "Digits in a^n = floor(n x log10(a)) + 1\nlog(2)=0.301 log(3)=0.477 log(5)=0.699 log(7)=0.845\n\nSqrt estimation: sqrt(N) ~ p + (N-p^2)/(2p)\n  where p^2 is nearest perfect square <= N\n\nPerfect square: unit digit 0,1,4,5,6,9 only\n  digital root must be 1,4,7,9\n\nWHY: A number with d digits satisfies\n10^(d-1)<=a^n<10^d\n  Taking log: d-1<=n×log(a)<d → d=floor(n×log(a))+1\n\nEx: Digits in 5^20 = floor(20×0.699)+1 =\nfloor(13.98)+1 = 14 ✓",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 2000,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 20,
      "isDeleted": false,
