    },
    {
      "id": "el_36",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1005,
      "y": 781,
      "width": 267,
      "height": 216,
      "text": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: 4^x = 32\n  (2^2)^x = 2^5 → 2^(2x) = 2^5\nStep 2: 2x = 5 → x = 2.5\n\nTRICK:\nConvert to same base (usually 2 or 3)\n4=2², 32=2⁵ → equate exponents\n2x=5 → x=2.5\n\n  4^x = 32\n  (2^2)^x = 2^5\n   2^2x   = 2^5  → 2x=5 → x=2.5\n\nAnswer: x = 2.5 ✓",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 12,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 3600,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 36,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "type_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: 4^x = 32\n  (2^2)^x = 2^5 → 2^(2x) = 2^5\nStep 2: 2x = 5 → x = 2.5\n\nTRICK:\nConvert to same base (usually 2 or 3)\n4=2², 32=2⁵ → equate exponents\n2x=5 → x=2.5\n\n  4^x = 32\n  (2^2)^x = 2^5\n   2^2x   = 2^5  → 2x=5 → x=2.5\n\nAnswer: x = 2.5 ✓",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
