    {
      "id": "el_86",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 65,
      "y": 2290,
      "width": 274,
      "height": 216,
      "text": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: Digits = floor(n×log10(a)) + 1\n  = floor(100×0.3010) + 1\nStep 2: = floor(30.10) + 1 = 31\n\nTRICK:\nDigits = floor(n×log(a)) + 1\nlog(2)=0.301 log(3)=0.477\nlog(5)=0.699 log(7)=0.845\n\n  Digits = floor(100 × 0.301) + 1\n         = floor(30.1) + 1\n         = 30 + 1 = 31\n\nAnswer: 2^100 has 31 digits ✓",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 12,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 8600,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 86,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "type_13"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: Digits = floor(n×log10(a)) + 1\n  = floor(100×0.3010) + 1\nStep 2: = floor(30.10) + 1 = 31\n\nTRICK:\nDigits = floor(n×log(a)) + 1\nlog(2)=0.301 log(3)=0.477\nlog(5)=0.699 log(7)=0.845\n\n  Digits = floor(100 × 0.301) + 1\n         = floor(30.1) + 1\n         = 30 + 1 = 31\n\nAnswer: 2^100 has 31 digits ✓",
